dig%20out%20about%20three%20or%20four%20feet%20in%20someone's%20backyard%2C%20for%20example%2C%20and%20then%20put%20in%20a%20structure%20that%20is%20maybe%20three%20or%20four%20feet%20above%20the%20ground.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20the%20ultimate%20option%20is%20a%20fully%20submerged%20solution%2C%20but%20those%20are%20a%20lot%20more%20expensive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShelters%20are%20not%20as%20romantic%20as%20in%20the%20movies.%20They%20are%20normally%20about%2010%20feet%20wide%20and%2020%20to%2040%20feet%20long.%20The%20majority%20of%20my%20clients%20are%20upper%20middle%20class%2C%20and%20they%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BWell%2C%20instead%20of%20getting%20the%20nicest%20Mercedes%2C%20I%20could%20use%20the%20extra%20%2440%2C000%20on%20a%20solution%20that%20could%20save%20my%20family's%20life.%26quot%3B%20They%20rationalize%20it%20that%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20had%20some%20people%20contact%20me%20for%20larger%20shelters%2C%20but%20those%20are%20executive%2C%20C-suite-level%20people.%20They're%20not%20household%20names%2C%20but%20you%20look%20them%20up%20and%20find%20they're%20the%20CEO%20or%20COO%20of%20a%20company.%20Their%20budget%20is%20much%20higher.%20They%20don't%20seem%20to%20mind%20spending%20well%20into%20six%20figures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20clients%20don't%20want%20to%20tell%20their%20neighbors%20because%20they're%20nosy.%20They%20don't%20want%20to%20tell%20their%20homeowners%20association%20because%20then%20everyone's%20going%20to%20want%20to%20go%20there%20in%20case%20of%20an%20emergency.%20They%20think%2C%20%26quot%3BThey're%20my%20neighbor%2C%20why%20wouldn't%20they%20open%20up%20their%20vault%20door%20for%20me%3F%20I've%20been%20their%20neighbor%20for%2015%20years.%26quot%3B%20It's%20a%20sensitive%20topic%20for%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20discretion%20is%20a%20requirement%20for%20our%20construction%20projects.%20We%20have%20a%20few%20different%20fake%20magnetic%20company%20decals%20to%20put%20on%20the%20side%20of%20the%20trucks%2C%20like%20pool%20guys%20or%20solar%20installers.%20Sometimes%20I%20offer%20to%20put%20up%20a%20big%20construction%20tent.%20We%20also%20disguise%20the%20shelter%20itself.%20Sometimes%20it%20looks%20like%20a%20shed%20or%20a%20doghouse.%20I%20like%20to%20make%20a%20trellis%20because%20that%20will%20keep%20most%20people%20from%20paying%20attention%20to%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20aren't%20going%20to%20be%20staying%20in%20these%20things%20for%20years%2C%20or%20decades%2C%20or%20months%2C%20even.%20After%20a%20week%2C%20the%20radioactivity%20level%20drops%20substantially%2C%20and%20moving%20around%20is%20considered%20safer.%20After%20three%20weeks%2C%20there's%20hardly%20any%20remnants%2C%20and%20it's%20relatively%20safe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20two%20parts%20of%20a%20nuclear%20blast%20that%20are%20a%20concern.%20The%20initial%20blast%20has%20high-velocity%20winds%20and%20heat.%20A%20lot%20of%20people%20would%20die%20from%20that%20without%20shelter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20generally%20speaking%2C%20there%20are%20between%2030%20minutes%20and%2075%20minutes%20before%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnuclear-bomb-attack-russia-ukraine-how-strong-far-2022-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efallout%3C%2Fa%3E%20starts.%20Fallout%20is%20just%20the%20dust%20that%20settles%20from%20the%20explosion%2C%20but%20radioactive%20particles%20attach%20to%20that%20dust.%20It%20makes%20this%20dirty%20snow%20that%20sort%20of%20seems%20like%20ash.%20That's%20what%20is%20going%20to%20be%20dangerous%20for%20the%20next%20three%20weeks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20people%20survive%20that%20first%20blast%2C%20that's%20great.%20Then%20they%20have%20one%20to%20three%20weeks%20where%20they%20really%20need%20to%20be%20sheltered%20in%20place%20and%20not%20go%20anywhere.%20And%20that%20is%20the%20ultimate%20goal%20of%20the%20service%20that%20we%20provide%3A%20a%20safe%20place%20for%20people%20and%20their%20loved%20ones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%2